title: [Bath House, Stern Corridor]
description: Forming a striped pattern, the floor of the corridor has mahogany and teak boards laid diagonally from northeast to southwest.  Stained sky lights, recessed into the ceiling, allow the golden light of the day to illuminate the room, while an enormous filigree-edged arch in the southern wall leads to the bathing annexes.
